1
00:00:04,970 --> 00:00:06,230
The sun needs rest too.

2
00:00:07,440 --> 00:00:08,770
If it shone all the time,

3
00:00:09,040 --> 00:00:09,700
the plants

4
00:00:10,170 --> 00:00:11,070
would wither,

5
00:00:12,170 --> 00:00:12,970
and the rivers

6
00:00:13,240 --> 00:00:13,980
would dry up.

7
00:00:17,750 --> 00:00:20,520
We all carry fear inside us.

8
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:24,290
Fear can keep us from moving forward.

9
00:00:38,430 --> 00:00:39,530
That's when

10
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,740
we have to find our strength again

11
00:00:42,440 --> 00:00:45,040
and take that first brave step.

12
00:00:55,950 --> 00:00:56,950
When I'm with you,

13
00:00:57,220 --> 00:00:58,490
I feel recharged.

14
00:01:04,660 --> 00:01:05,190
Then,

15
00:01:05,550 --> 00:01:06,680
why don't we write down that feeling

16
00:01:06,680 --> 00:01:08,010
while it's still fresh?

17
00:01:14,370 --> 00:01:15,240
Here?

18
00:01:17,170 --> 00:01:18,240
The truest feelings

19
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:19,970
are the ones you have right now.

20
00:01:29,470 --> 00:01:30,320
This time,

21
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:31,690
I don't want to write about

22
00:01:31,690 --> 00:01:33,150
what I've lost.

23
00:01:33,460 --> 00:01:34,360
I want to

24
00:01:34,539 --> 00:01:36,600
write about what I still have to give.

25
00:02:39,829 --> 00:02:45,070
[Smile After Tears]

26
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:51,020
[Chapter Eleven: A Chorus of Courage]

27
00:03:08,150 --> 00:03:09,420
This time really is different.

28
00:03:09,420 --> 00:03:11,120
The music finally feels right.

29
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:12,380
You guys were amazing!

30
00:03:14,220 --> 00:03:15,280
That's wonderful.

31
00:03:16,690 --> 00:03:18,550
I'll submit the demo later today.

32
00:03:22,290 --> 00:03:24,350
[Learning Knows No Bounds.
Education Is for All.]

33
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:27,640
Sir,

34
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:28,850
this is the class assignment.

35
00:03:28,850 --> 00:03:29,340
Okay.

36
00:03:30,110 --> 00:03:31,170
Junjia, come here.

37
00:03:32,110 --> 00:03:32,570
Come.

38
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:35,840
[Manhattan School of Music]

39
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,050
What is this?

40
00:03:37,380 --> 00:03:38,050
The school has received

41
00:03:38,050 --> 00:03:39,110
a notice about an exchange program

42
00:03:39,110 --> 00:03:40,820
with the Manhattan School of Music.

43
00:03:40,820 --> 00:03:42,620
I think you're an excellent fit.

44
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:45,450
Your English is strong,

45
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:47,490
your grades are outstanding,
and you're fully qualified.

46
00:03:47,490 --> 00:03:48,460
It's a rare opportunity,

47
00:03:48,460 --> 00:03:50,260
so give it some serious thought.

48
00:03:53,230 --> 00:03:53,829
That's it.

49
00:03:55,329 --> 00:04:00,090
[Exchange Student]

50
00:04:04,710 --> 00:04:05,640
This one's on me.

51
00:04:07,410 --> 00:04:08,380
And

52
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:09,680
thanks

53
00:04:10,010 --> 00:04:11,610
for helping me the other day.

54
00:04:11,980 --> 00:04:13,010
You don't have to.

55
00:04:19,839 --> 00:04:20,810
Welcome.

56
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:35,710
Don't come over!

57
00:04:35,710 --> 00:04:36,730
Don't come over!

58
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:37,610
Well,

59
00:04:37,790 --> 00:04:39,050
sorry for scaring you.

60
00:04:39,340 --> 00:04:40,740
I'm Junjia's classmate.

61
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:42,180
My name is Zheng Diaoqin.

62
00:04:44,750 --> 00:04:46,990
You should've said you were human!

63
00:04:47,630 --> 00:04:49,350
Don't creep around like that!

64
00:04:50,620 --> 00:04:51,920
No wonder Junjia said

65
00:04:51,950 --> 00:04:53,610
you're hilarious to talk to.

66
00:04:54,690 --> 00:04:56,090
I guess I am pretty funny.

67
00:04:56,390 --> 00:04:57,650
That didn't sound like

68
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:59,260
a compliment.

69
00:05:01,830 --> 00:05:03,260
The tricks I taught you

70
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:05,030
worked pretty well, didn't they?

71
00:05:05,030 --> 00:05:06,000
Well...

72
00:05:06,930 --> 00:05:08,240
they did help Junjia.

73
00:05:09,270 --> 00:05:10,670
Help Junjia,

74
00:05:11,340 --> 00:05:12,540
or help the two of you?

75
00:05:16,180 --> 00:05:17,010
Excuse me.

76
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:18,710
Welcome.

77
00:05:19,380 --> 00:05:20,210
Is this

78
00:05:20,210 --> 00:05:21,920
where Junjia works?

79
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,590
Junjia, time to eat.

80
00:05:33,460 --> 00:05:34,330
Diaoqin!

81
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:35,530
Our demo got through.

82
00:05:35,530 --> 00:05:36,600
We advanced.

83
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:38,000
Seriously?

84
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:38,730
Yes.

85
00:05:38,730 --> 00:05:40,540
The organizers just texted us.

86
00:05:41,170 --> 00:05:41,970
That's great!

87
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,100
You did it!

88
00:05:43,470 --> 00:05:45,000
I have to thank you for this.

89
00:05:45,710 --> 00:05:47,840
Let me see what other groups there are.

90
00:05:50,340 --> 00:05:51,100
By the way,

91
00:05:52,150 --> 00:05:54,220
I heard about the exchange program.

92
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:56,280
How did you know?

93
00:05:57,650 --> 00:05:58,390
Well,

94
00:06:00,090 --> 00:06:02,490
people in class have been
talking about it.

95
00:06:05,570 --> 00:06:06,680
So,

96
00:06:08,170 --> 00:06:10,120
he's been staying at your place?

97
00:06:11,610 --> 00:06:12,170
Yes.

98
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:16,100
It's good that he's with a classmate.

99
00:06:19,230 --> 00:06:20,560
Has he been eating well?

100
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:24,680
I'm just asking.

101
00:06:28,910 --> 00:06:30,480
Junjia

102
00:06:30,820 --> 00:06:32,190
is stubborn,

103
00:06:34,430 --> 00:06:35,860
but he's a good kid.

104
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:40,340
And here I am, a grown-up,

105
00:06:40,570 --> 00:06:42,690
too embarrassed to call him

106
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:46,700
after our argument.

107
00:06:49,470 --> 00:06:50,409
I'm not sure

108
00:06:50,830 --> 00:06:52,730
if he even wants to hear my voice.

109
00:07:01,070 --> 00:07:03,010
The school called.

110
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,530
They said there's an

111
00:07:05,150 --> 00:07:08,860
exchange program
with the Manhattan School of Music.

112
00:07:10,290 --> 00:07:12,530
But Junjia turned it down.

113
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:16,600
An exchange program?

114
00:07:18,930 --> 00:07:19,770
To the U.S.?

115
00:07:20,260 --> 00:07:20,960
Yes.

116
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,170
Didn't Junjia tell you?

117
00:07:29,490 --> 00:07:30,990
I just

118
00:07:32,540 --> 00:07:34,000
turned my professor down.

119
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:38,690
It just doesn't

120
00:07:38,690 --> 00:07:40,320
feel like the right time.

121
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:43,420
There's still too much
I can't leave behind.

122
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:46,170
I have to work,

123
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:47,600
rehearse with the band,

124
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,860
and keep making music.

125
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:51,790
And if I leave,

126
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:54,159
what will happen to my aunt?

127
00:07:56,830 --> 00:07:59,480
I want him to have a better life.

128
00:08:02,130 --> 00:08:04,190
I don't want him struggling like I do—

129
00:08:04,210 --> 00:08:06,070
constantly worrying about money

130
00:08:06,580 --> 00:08:08,780
and wondering how we're going to get by.

131
00:08:10,890 --> 00:08:12,220
I can't give him that.

132
00:08:17,220 --> 00:08:20,020
Now that this opportunity
is right in front of him,

133
00:08:20,660 --> 00:08:22,100
he still won't take it.

134
00:08:25,730 --> 00:08:27,930
I know he has things he's worried about.

135
00:08:34,940 --> 00:08:36,409
You're his good friend.

136
00:08:37,830 --> 00:08:39,900
I hope you can talk to him.

137
00:08:47,290 --> 00:08:48,450
I just want

138
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:50,160
him to have a better life.

139
00:08:50,890 --> 00:08:53,420
-If you could try to persuade him...
-Auntie,

140
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:55,460
I don't think

141
00:08:56,530 --> 00:08:57,790
I can promise you that.

142
00:09:00,650 --> 00:09:02,930
If it's not what he truly wants,

143
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:05,310
he'll only

144
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,040
end up miserable.

145
00:09:12,350 --> 00:09:14,280
But I know you're doing this

146
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:16,540
because you want what's best for Junjia.

147
00:09:16,650 --> 00:09:18,950
My parents often tell me the same thing.

148
00:09:19,590 --> 00:09:20,390
But,

149
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:22,920
they also tell me

150
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:24,990
that instead of pushing me down

151
00:09:24,990 --> 00:09:26,650
a path that only looks better,

152
00:09:27,090 --> 00:09:28,400
they'd rather have someone

153
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:31,130
walk with me and help me
find the path I truly want.

154
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,510
Taking that first step

155
00:09:37,970 --> 00:09:39,010
is never easy.

156
00:09:42,210 --> 00:09:43,070
Actually,

157
00:09:43,340 --> 00:09:44,540
I'm also very scared.

158
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:46,810
If I take that step forward,

159
00:09:47,490 --> 00:09:50,090
what if I end up losing something
along the way?

160
00:10:02,850 --> 00:10:03,910
By the way, Junjia,

161
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:05,000
there's something

162
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,080
I need to tell you.

163
00:10:06,250 --> 00:10:07,700
I met with your aunt.

164
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:10,000
She's really worried about you.

165
00:10:26,090 --> 00:10:27,150
Thank you.

166
00:10:49,110 --> 00:10:49,840
Hey.

167
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:52,180
Hey.

168
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:55,780
Um...

169
00:10:58,560 --> 00:10:59,290
You first.

170
00:11:00,590 --> 00:11:01,490
You go first.

171
00:11:03,390 --> 00:11:04,090
It's okay.

172
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,210
You go first.

173
00:11:06,660 --> 00:11:07,430
Diaoqin,

174
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,000
thank you.

175
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:11,820
You're thanking me again?

176
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:14,520
Ever since the beginning,

177
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:16,000
you've taken me in.

178
00:11:17,580 --> 00:11:18,460
And when

179
00:11:18,940 --> 00:11:20,370
my aunt went to see you,

180
00:11:21,860 --> 00:11:22,860
she told me

181
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:24,340
how much you cared about me

182
00:11:24,610 --> 00:11:25,810
and how you said so many things to her,

183
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:26,350
right?

184
00:11:29,180 --> 00:11:30,780
I just want you to know

185
00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:35,650
that no matter what difficulties you face,

186
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:37,750
no matter what happens,

187
00:11:39,130 --> 00:11:40,390
I will always be there.

188
00:11:42,030 --> 00:11:42,800
I know.

189
00:11:45,270 --> 00:11:46,270
Do you know

190
00:11:50,270 --> 00:11:51,370
that I like you?

191
00:12:06,620 --> 00:12:07,390
It's just

192
00:12:08,060 --> 00:12:09,060
that I don't know

193
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:13,160
if my answer

194
00:12:14,030 --> 00:12:15,630
is the one you're hoping for.

195
00:12:16,230 --> 00:12:17,470
How would you know

196
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:20,570
what kind of answer I'm hoping for?

197
00:12:22,190 --> 00:12:24,120
After talking with you for so long,

198
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:26,040
the one thing I expect the least

199
00:12:26,410 --> 00:12:27,460
is an answer.

200
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:28,910
Sometimes,

201
00:12:30,030 --> 00:12:31,090
happiness

202
00:12:31,950 --> 00:12:33,310
is having someone

203
00:12:33,950 --> 00:12:35,350
who will always love you,

204
00:12:35,420 --> 00:12:37,580
and having someone

205
00:12:39,020 --> 00:12:40,820
you can love with all your heart.

206
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:44,260
Actually,

207
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:47,260
I think both of us

208
00:12:47,830 --> 00:12:49,230
really need courage.

209
00:12:52,130 --> 00:12:52,800
So,

210
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:56,250
I want to be the strength you can lean on

211
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:59,000
when you don't have enough courage.

212
00:12:59,000 --> 00:12:59,810
But

213
00:13:00,430 --> 00:13:02,490
I don't know how long

214
00:13:03,810 --> 00:13:05,210
it will take me to move on.

215
00:13:06,270 --> 00:13:07,330
I will wait for you.

216
00:13:11,490 --> 00:13:13,720
From now on, we're friends.

217
00:13:17,790 --> 00:13:20,030
Time has separated us for so long.

218
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:23,000
My love for you

219
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:25,860
has never changed.

220
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:37,010
What are you doing here?

221
00:13:37,010 --> 00:13:38,000
It's dangerous.

222
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,730
Whatever's troubling you,

223
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:47,590
tell me

224
00:13:47,590 --> 00:13:48,820
when you're ready.

225
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:50,730
So

226
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:52,290
stay

227
00:13:52,640 --> 00:13:53,700
as long as you want.

228
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,730
Junjia!

229
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:17,280
Auntie,

230
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:18,890
don't worry.

231
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:21,580
No matter what happens,

232
00:14:22,860 --> 00:14:24,530
I'll stay by Junjia's side

233
00:14:24,890 --> 00:14:25,970
and accompany him.

234
00:14:33,230 --> 00:14:33,930
Junjia,

235
00:14:35,140 --> 00:14:36,100
do you

236
00:14:38,510 --> 00:14:40,010
really want to go abroad?

237
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:49,760
Even if you truly lose something
along the way,

238
00:14:50,310 --> 00:14:52,120
I'll be the person

239
00:14:53,420 --> 00:14:54,490
you can turn around and see

240
00:14:54,490 --> 00:14:55,950
whenever you need me most.

241
00:15:00,690 --> 00:15:03,020
It doesn't matter
if you're not by my side.

242
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:04,320
At least

243
00:15:04,350 --> 00:15:06,390
when I need them,

244
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:07,570
they are the ones

245
00:15:07,570 --> 00:15:09,470
that I can see when I turn back.

246
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:11,850
They are in my heart.

247
00:15:12,710 --> 00:15:13,570
That's enough.

248
00:15:20,510 --> 00:15:22,150
I'd forgotten

249
00:15:23,450 --> 00:15:25,810
I'd once said those very same words.

250
00:15:32,190 --> 00:15:33,260
It turns out

251
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:36,810
that when we're consumed by fear,

252
00:15:36,980 --> 00:15:40,600
we forget that we once had courage too.

253
00:15:43,540 --> 00:15:44,570
Maybe

254
00:15:45,010 --> 00:15:47,940
courage isn't something
we're meant to carry alone.

255
00:15:47,940 --> 00:15:49,940
Maybe it's something

256
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:52,900
that slowly awakens
when someone is by our side.

257
00:16:09,030 --> 00:16:09,630
Everyone.

258
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:10,520
Come on!

259
00:16:10,680 --> 00:16:11,570
Gather around.

260
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:12,370
Come on.

261
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,690
The competition is this weekend.

262
00:16:17,690 --> 00:16:19,290
No matter what the result is,

263
00:16:19,310 --> 00:16:19,970
I just want us

264
00:16:19,970 --> 00:16:21,230
to remember one thing:

265
00:16:21,910 --> 00:16:24,200
We're walking onto that stage together.

266
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:25,680
So whatever happens,

267
00:16:25,820 --> 00:16:26,900
don't panic.

268
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:28,650
All it takes is one look at each other,

269
00:16:28,650 --> 00:16:30,780
and we'll know exactly what to do next.

270
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:32,450
I believe

271
00:16:32,610 --> 00:16:34,080
that's our chemistry.

272
00:16:35,910 --> 00:16:37,000
No problem.

273
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:38,870
Let's do our team cheer.

274
00:16:39,090 --> 00:16:39,690
Come on.

275
00:16:39,930 --> 00:16:40,760
BACKSPACE!

276
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:42,700
Go, go, go!

277
00:16:50,370 --> 00:16:51,370
Our band's performing

278
00:16:51,370 --> 00:16:52,470
this weekend.

279
00:16:52,770 --> 00:16:53,710
You have to come.

280
00:16:54,110 --> 00:16:54,540
Okay.

281
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:55,360
I will.

282
00:16:56,210 --> 00:16:56,840
Diaoqin,

283
00:16:58,810 --> 00:17:00,050
you're right.

284
00:17:01,980 --> 00:17:02,950
The sun

285
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:04,599
needs to rest too.

286
00:17:06,849 --> 00:17:09,490
Even though it looks the same every day,

287
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:14,060
it's still beautiful.

288
00:17:47,780 --> 00:17:51,500
[To Junjia]

289
00:18:05,110 --> 00:18:08,040
All these years,
I haven't been able to give you much.

290
00:18:08,150 --> 00:18:10,150
I could only save a little at a time.

291
00:18:11,620 --> 00:18:13,150
I know it's not much,

292
00:18:13,150 --> 00:18:16,150
but at least it'll help you go abroad
and see the world.

293
00:18:17,420 --> 00:18:20,000
And don't think you can get away
without paying me back.

294
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,440
When you make it big someday,

295
00:18:22,470 --> 00:18:24,000
you'd better pay me back.

296
